{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform Universal Credit rules for people claiming Carer's Allowance.",
        "additional_details": "Pay the same rate of Universal Credit to people aged 18 to 24 claiming Carer's Allowance, as paid to those 25 and over.\r\n \r\nWe want the Government to better recognise people who provide unpaid care. Our job is hard enough providing care. This isn't a nine to five job it's round the clock and current rules for Universal Credit - deducting Carer's Allowance in full from entitlements, and paying a reduced rate to claimants aged under 25 - can make it hard for people on Carer's Allowance to afford to survive.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to:\r\n\r\nStop taking Carer's Allowance pound for pound off people's Universal Credit claims and take 55p for every pound instead.",
